what do i do about this gnome living in my basement i have this magical gnome that lives in my basement he keeps threatening to burn my house down other times he pees in my shoes just to be an a hole i have asked him to leave a few times but the jerk won't go he won't even split the utility bill anybody out there know how to kill a gnome or at least make him leave my house i already tried sending him to rehab i told him he has a drinking problem and the little b stard hit me i offer my back yard as a foster home for your gnome i have never turned a gnome away yet tell the gnome to expect company he will have to adjust to the idea of a water feature raspberry bushes birds butterflies some sneaky moths and various creepy crawlies he is not to bother my vegetable beds but he can pick as much rhubarb as he likes and of course he may sniff my flowers at will and once in while it hails so tell him to bring a hard hat and by the way he must not move my garden tools when i'm using them if i step on my trowel or hand rake i'll know it was him then there would be consequences Shannara creatures The Silence of the Lambs Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an RuneScape quests 1957 World Series Poker jargon RuneScape locations Piccolo Junior Saga Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Blackjack Gnome Sin City Dog training RuneScape skills Shannara Druids Customs and etiquette of Japan About a Boy Races in the Warcraft universe Charles Peace Avenue Q Nico Robin Knife Three Stooges The Time Machine Brewery The Shining (film) Slackware Kyoryuu Sentai ZyuRanger Drill bit Knots Landing Garfield U.S. presidential election, 2000 Alcoholics Anonymous Blankets (graphic novel) Textile manufacturing RuneScape economy The Amber Spyglass Final Fantasy magic Los Angeles Dodgers Bob Dole Gaia Online Bedknobs and Broomsticks Sento Colony in Space Dungeons & Dragons: Shadow over Mystara Windows XP One Tree Hill (TV series) Sacrifice (computer game) Pysanka Marching band Hell's Kitchen (television) E